Kairos cross-language golden fixtures (Track RF1).

Each file below pins a cross-language contract EXACTLY as the code produces it
today. Multiple language sides read the SAME file; corrupting one byte fails the
consumer tests on both sides. This is the same discipline as the capnp wire
goldens (*_golden_envelope.bin, read by core/tests/golden_wire.rs and
sidecar/concords/tests/test_golden*.cpp).

Consumers locate a fixture the same way the wire golden does: C++ via a
KAIROS_*_PATH compile definition (absolute, from CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR); Rust
via include_str!/include_bytes! of CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR/../schema/testdata/<file>.

quote_golden_envelope.bin / quote_v2_golden_envelope.bin / trade_golden_envelope.bin
  Frozen capnp Envelope wire format. Regeneration: sidecar test_golden_v2 /
  test_golden emit paths (see sidecar/concords/tests).

runtime_paths.txt
  Contract: env>XDG>run-user UDS/sentinel path resolution (core resolve, exec
  ResolveSock, tui halt/hub_status/supervisor resolve). Regeneration: hand-edited
  table (schema/testdata/gen is not used); columns documented in the file header.
  Consumers: core uds::path test, exec test_socket_path, tui halt/hub_status/
  supervisor golden tests.

trading_days.txt
  Contract: UTC+8 trading-date (yyyymmdd) and Taipei hhmm from an epoch-us
  timestamp (exec TradingDayUtc8/TradingDayNumUtc8/HhmmFromUs, core yyyymmdd_utc8
  + tapegen::hhmm_from_us, tui civil_from_days). Regeneration: run test_trading_days
  with KAIROS_REGEN=1 (writes the file from the C++ canonical helper). Consumers:
  exec test_trading_days, core recorder test, tui order_journal date test.

journal_corpus.jsonl / journal_expected.txt
  Contract: order-journal JSONL as the C++ writers emit it (OrderJournal::Log* and
  OrderFlowJournal::Append*), incl. hostile-string escaping and the err truncation
  cap. The clock-derived "t" field is masked to 0 in the committed corpus.
  Regeneration: run test_journal_corpus with KAIROS_REGEN=1. journal_expected.txt
  is the per-line decoded-value table the tui parser must reproduce. Consumers:
  exec test_journal_corpus (regenerate + byte-compare), tui order_journal golden test.

ctl_corpus.txt
  Contract: scenario-ctl JSON-lines protocol. SNAP<TAB> lines are
  SerializeScenarioSnapshot outputs (all states, restart_count/gave_up, hostile
  last_exit_reason); REQ<TAB> lines are tui list/start/stop request builders.
  Regeneration: run test_ctl_corpus with KAIROS_REGEN=1. Consumers: exec
  test_ctl_corpus (regenerate SNAP + parse REQ), tui ctl_corpus integration test
  (parse SNAP + regenerate REQ).
